oks Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Preston Library Preston Library Library Home Library Home Find Books Find Books Departments Departments Media Equipment Media Equipment Technical Services Technical Services Visitor Information Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Archives Archives Archives Home Archives Home Online Exhibits Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Civil War   New Market Give Give Close Menu Academics Home Jackson Hope Fund Video Testimonies Jackson Hope Stories Initiatives Funding Process About the Fund History Membership Jackson Hope Fund Warren J  Bryan  71 VMI Foundation  Inc  Ph   540  464 7287 bbryan vmiaa org Academics P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office 210 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Institute Report  June 2008  Eight VMI professors will be on leave for the 2008 09 year  Lt  Col  Charles Bott will research biological nutrient removal through a Wachtmeister Faculty Development leave  Maj  Dennis Foster will research the relationship between the legislative and executive branches on issues of coercive foreign policy through an Ayres Faculty Development Leave  and Col  Myke Gluck will assess computer forensics software usability with applications to VMI computer science and the science and security programs through a VMI Awards Faculty Development Leave  Jackson Hope Faculty Development leaves have been awarded to Lt  Col  Mary Ann Dellinger  who will work on  The Muse Unchained  Politics  Prison  and Poetry in Franco s Spain  Lt  Col  Matt Hyre  who will work on numerical modeling of glass forming processes and the development of reconstructed simulation environments  Lt  Col  Tinni Sen  who will research anticipated future changes under state dependent pricing rules  Lt  Col  Daren Timmons  who will research flavonoids in crystal engineering  and Col  Bruce Vandervort  who is writing a book on the Italian invasion and conquest of Libya in 1911 Academics Home Jackson Hope Fund Video Testimonies Jackson Hope Stories Initiatives Funding Process About the Fund History Membership Jackson Hope Fund Warren J  Bryan  71 VMI Foundation  Inc  Ph   540  464 7287 bbryan vmiaa org Academics P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office 210 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450  Academics Home Jackson Hope Fund Video Testimonies Jackson Hope Stories Initiatives Funding Process About the Fund History Membership Jackson Hope Fund Warren J  Bryan  71 VMI Foundation  Inc  Ph   540  464 7287 bbryan vmiaa org Academics P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office 210 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Academics Home Jackson Hope Fund Video Testimonies Jackson Hope Stories Initiatives Funding Process About the Fund History Membership Academics Home Academics Home Jackson Hope Fund Jackson Hope Fund Video Testimonies Video Testimonies Jackson Hope Stories Jackson Hope Stories Initiatives Initiatives Funding Process Funding Process About the Fund About the Fund History History Membership Membership Jackson Hope Fund Warren J  Bryan  71 VMI Foundation  Inc  Ph   540  464 7287 bbryan vmiaa org Academics P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office 210 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Jackson Hope Fund Warren J  Bryan  71 VMI Foundation  Inc  Ph   540  464 7287 bbryan vmiaa org Academics P   540  464 7212 F   540  464 7719 Dean s Office 210 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Jackson Hope Fund      bbryan vmiaa org   Academics           Institute Report  June 2008  Eight VMI professors will be on leave for the 2008 09 year  Lt  Col  Charles Bott will research biological nutrient removal through a Wachtmeister Faculty Development leave  Maj  Dennis Foster will research the relationship between the legislative and executive branches on issues of coercive foreign policy through an Ayres Faculty Development Leave  and Col  Myke Gluck will assess computer forensics software usability with applications to VMI computer science and the science and security programs through a VMI Awards Faculty Development Leave  Jackson Hope Faculty Development leaves have been awarded to Lt  Col  Mary Ann Dellinger  who will work on  The Muse Unchained  Politics  Prison  and Poetry in Franco s Spain  Lt  Col  Matt Hyre  who will work on numerical modeling of glass forming processes and the development of reconstructed simulation environments  Lt  Col  Tinni Sen  who will research anticipated future changes under state dependent pricing rules  Lt  Col  Daren Timmons  who will research flavonoids in crystal engineering  and Col  Bruce Vandervort  who is writing a book on the Italian invasion and conquest of Libya in 1911      Institute Report  June 2008  Eight VMI professors will be on leave for the 2008 09 year  Lt  Col  Charles Bott will research biological nutrient removal through a Wachtmeister Faculty Development leave  Maj  Dennis Foster will research the relationship between the legislative and executive branches on issues of coercive foreign policy through an Ayres Faculty Development Leave  and Col  Myke Gluck will assess computer forensics software usability with applications to VMI computer science and the science and security programs through a VMI Awards Faculty Development Leave  Jackson Hope Faculty Development leaves have been awarded to Lt  Col  Mary Ann Dellinger  who will work on  The Muse Unchained  Politics  Prison  and Poetry in Franco s Spain  Lt  Col  Matt Hyre  who will work on numerical modeling of glass f